ngress.kubernetes.io/affinity\\`\n- Any custom snippet annotations (\\`configuration-snippet\\`, \\`server-snippet\\`)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\n- [ ] **Snapshot current state**\n  \\`\\`\\`\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup/deploy.yaml\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup/configmap.yaml\n  kubectl -n demo get ingress -o yaml > backup/ingress-demo.yaml\n  kubectl get ingressclass -o yaml > backup/ingressclasses.yaml\n  \\`\\`\\`\n- [ ] Record current controller image digest (\\`kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ... -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'\\`)\n- [ ] Confirm the target version's release notes: check for removed/changed annotations and ConfigMap keys\n- [ ] Check Kubernetes version compatibility matrix for the target ingress-nginx version\n- [ ] Verify cluster has capacity for a rolling restart (at least 1 spare replica slot)\n- [ ] If \\`allow-snippet-annotations\\` was set, note it may default to \\`false\\` in newer versions\n- [ ] Alert on-call for the maintenance window\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Steps\n\n### Step 1 — Pull the new manifests\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nTARGET_VERSION=<next-version>   # e.g., 1.11.5 — confirm from release page\nkubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/controller-v\\${TARGET_VERSION}/deploy/static/provider/kind/deploy.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n> For non-kind clusters replace \\`kind\\` with \\`cloud\\` or \\`baremetal\\` as appropriate.\n\n### Step 2 — Re-apply the ConfigMap overrides\nThe \\`apply\\` above may reset the controller ConfigMap. Re-apply every non-default key:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch configmap ingress-nginx-controller --patch-file backup/configmap-patch.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\nWhere \\`configmap-patch.yaml\\` contains only the delta keys (do NOT copy deprecated keys; map them to their new names first).\n\n### Step 3 — Re-apply the deployment extra args\nIf controller \\`args\\` differ from the upstream default, patch the Deployment:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deploy ingress-nginx-controller --patch-file backup/deploy-args-patch.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 4 — Verify the IngressClasses remain intact\nThe three IngressClasses (\\`nginx\\`, \\`ingress-1\\`, \\`ingress-2\\`) are cluster-scoped and survive namespace-level upgrades, but verify:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get ingressclass\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 5 — Wait for rollout\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=5m\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 6 — Smoke-test the demo app\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n demo get ingress\ncurl -v -H 'Host: <demo-host>' http://<node-ip>:<nodePort>/\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 7 — Validate logs\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=100\n\\`\\`\\`\nLook for: no \\`FATAL\\` errors, correct upstream endpoints resolved, expected \\`log-format-upstream\\` output.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Known Annotation & ConfigMap Breaking Changes to Check\n\n| Old key / annotation | Status in >=1.10 | Action |\n|---|---|---|\n| \\`allow-snippet-annotations\\` ConfigMap key | Defaults to \\`false\\` since 1.9 | Set to \\`true\\` only if snippets are audited; prefer \\`nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/configuration-snippet\\` removal |\n| \\`ssl-dh-param\\` | Removed in 1.11 | Remove if present |\n| \\`use-regex\\` on path | Behaviour changed in 1.8 | Audit Ingress paths |\n| \\`nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/mirror-*\\` | Stable | No change needed |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nIf the new version causes regressions:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# Re-apply the saved deployment snapshot (restores image + args)\nkubectl apply -f backup/deploy.yaml\n# Re-apply the saved ConfigMap\nkubectl apply -f backup/configmap.yaml\n# Wait for rollback\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=5m\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Post-Upgrade Tasks\n\n- [ ] Update any CI/CD pipeline image references to the new version tag\n- [ ] Update internal runbooks with the new version\n- [ ] Remove the snapshot backups from \\`backup/\\` once the new version is stable for 48 h\n- [ ] Re-run any ingress-related integration tests\n\n---\n\n_Plan authored: 2026-06-14. Cluster: karma-b (kind, k8s v1.35.0). Status: PENDING REVIEW — no changes applied._\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in demo namespace with upgrade plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":687,"cache_read_input_tokens":37891,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":687},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8a413f5-583e-4492-9bc7-c952f85a82f4","uuid":"82016720-9b9e-413c-b106-506e6dade608","request_id":"req_011Cc2gQbJQKKq9FYYY1dbVD"}
